1. Download Windows 10
2. Create Server 2019 and in this case it is named DC
3. NIC dedicated to internet and one that is internal. Setup internal NIC manually as external NIC will be setup automatically from the home router.
4. Install Active Directory Domain Services and create a Domain
5. Create our own Domain account instead of using the built in domain account
6. Install RAS/NAT Remote Access Server/Network Address Translation which enables the Windows 10 client be in the private virtual network and also access the internet through the domain controller
7. DHCP scope to automatically allocate IP address to components of the network
8. Create the user accounts using Windows powershell
9. Set up the Client to be used by various user accounts   
